Package org.liris.smartgov.lez.core.agent.driver.behavior

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DeliveryDriverBehavior
    A delivery driver behavior, that can be described as follow : At initialization, the agent enters the origin establishment. The agent waits until the departure Date, and leave the origin. The agent navigate in the graph to reach all the round's establishment, using the shortest path, in order.
    DriverBehavior
    The generic class of driver behaviors.
    LezBehavior
    Abstract behavior that describes the behavior of an agent moving in an urban environment including a Low Emission Zone.
    PrivateDriverBehavior
    Generic class of behavior for private agents.
    RoundDeparture
    Event triggered when an agent leave its origin establishment to perform a round.
    RoundEnd
    Event triggered when an agent come back to its origin after a round.
    WorkerBehavior
    Behavior of worker private agent.
    WorkerHomeAtNoonBehavior
    Behavior of worker home at noon private agent.
    WorkerOneActivityBehavior
    Behavior of worker home at noon private agent.
